                    "body": "If you're under Linux, it's very easy to increase the maximum number of open files:\r\n{code:java}\r\n$ LANG=C ulimit --help\r\nulimit: ulimit [-SHabcdefiklmnpqrstuvxPT] [limit]\r\n    Modify shell resource limits.\r\n    \r\n[...]\r\n      -n\tthe maximum number of open file descriptors\r\n[...]\r\n$ ulimit -n \r\n1024\r\n$ ulimit -n 100000\r\n$ ulimit -n \r\n100000\r\n {code}\r\n\r\nSo I'm not convinced there's something Arrow should do here.",
